    "4).Predictive Accuracy:We analyze residuals between sampled worst-case obstacle clearances and ground truth.",
    "For each test case, we record the minimum absolute residual between samples from the predictive distribution and the ground truth, Table I shows that the r emp M M D -based augmented collision model (Fig. 5) surpasses the baseline (Fig.",
    "4) across all metrics: UR ↓50%, CR ↓80%, ES ↓74%, and ECE ↓20%.",
    "These gains stem from task-aware variance supervision aligning uncertainty with collision risk, unlike the NLL-only baseline(Fig. 4), which produces mis-calibrated and unreliable predictions.",
    "The same trend appears in navigation results (Table II), where the task-aware model reduces collisions by 4 times."
